Support in making process, product and customer audits: sustaining, documenting, evaluation, reporting and reaction;
Participation at the customer complaints analysis and proposal of corrective actions.

Monitoring and startup of corrective actions linked to the quality of the products recived from the customer / quality planning on the supplier side;
Supplier training with the requirements for APQP and PPAP;
Supplier visits and inspections for supplier approval;
Support given to the supplier for the approval of samples and prototypes;
Insuring and implementation of all the elements in the APQP;
Responsibility for organizing immediate measures in case of quality issues on the supplier side;
Following and checking of the effectiveness of corrective measures.

Opening and managing internal/external customer complaints in SAP;
Coordination of fast reaction and finalizing of root cause analysis, definition of measures and their validation;
Coordination of defining and implementation of the immediate actions and their documentation;
Planning of preventive actions;
Elaboration of the 8D report and submission to the customer;
Maintaining a permanent contact with the customer in topics related to customer complaints;
Following the implementation of corrective and preventive actions established and closing the 8D report;
Periodical elaboration and evaluation of kpi's for complaints(numer of complaints / claimed aspect / effectiveness of implemented actions),

Concurrently I am handling the following positions at SC Lustic Invest SA:  

(1)	Quality assurance team leader

(2)	Manager in charge of the finished products storage, packaging and delivery

(3)	Production coordinator

Accomplishments:

(1) Manager of the quality assurance activity in conformity with the European standards:

-	Realization and implementation of the quality assurance plan and lab analysis procedures in conformity with the relevant standards adopted by Romania: SR EN 572, SR EN 1036, SR EN 1096, SR EN 1279, SR EN 1863, SR 8572, SR EN 12150, SR EN 12543, SR EN 13022, SR EN 14179, SR EN 14449, SR EN 15434;
-	Procedures and process documents related to the quality assurance activity in the company;
-	Revision of the monitoring documentation based on the implemented quality assurance plan;
-	Revision of the product acceptance criteria. 

(2) Finished products department management including the activities related to the finished products storage, packaging and delivery:

-	Implementation of the electronic storage of finished products in stock and delivered;
-	Electronic storage management program that permits the exact localization of the finished products in stock or delivered;
-	The entire documentation for the organization and functioning of the storage department.
